sortes extenuatas. The sortes which thus ‘shrunk’ were slips of wood, on which proverbial phrases were written in archaic letters, and from which one or more were drawn at random when advice or guidance might be needed; cf. Cic. de divin. 11. 41. 69. The most famous were at Praeneste, 111 the temple of Fortuna, but in the lst Punic war a consul, who wished to consult them, was sternly forbidden by the senate.
